Introduction

Kim Jongseob, is a South Korean rapper, dancer, songwriter, and composer under FNC Entertainment. He is best known as the maknae of the boy group P1Harmony.

From December 2016 to April 2017, Jongseob participated in the competition show K-pop Star 6 and won as part of the duo, Boyfriend, with Park Hyun Jin. Following the show's conclusion, the duo signed a trainee contract with YG Entertainment. The following year, he join YG Treasure Box in Group C. However, he was eliminated in Episode 9.

On September 16, 2020, Jongseob was revealed as the first member of P1Harmony. The group officially debuted on October 28, 2020, with their first mini-album "Disharmony : Stand Out".
